pageContext.claim: “But their biggest year [China] was $16 billion in aggregate [agricultural imports from the U.S.]. That's a lot. Sixteen billion, that's a lot of corn. Sixteen billion was their biggest year. They're going to buy not 16, not 20, not 30, not 40. They're going to buy between 40 and $50 billion.”
pageContext.analysis: False. U.S. agricultural exports to China reached $26 billion in 2012, years before Trump's trade war depressed the numbers.
